---
// No Ghost props — copy is entirely hard-coded for this section.
---

<section class="bg-[color:var(--color-white)]">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="font-mono eyebrow text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[color:var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
      General Health Information
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl leading-snug text-[color:var(--color-ink)] mb-4 max-w-xl">
      What Are Peptide Therapies?
    </h2>
    <p class="text-base text-[color:var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-12">
      Peptides are short chains of amino acids that occur naturally in the body. They play a role in many biological
      processes. In clinical settings, certain peptide-based compounds are being explored as therapeutic options
      &mdash; and are available in Australia through regulated access pathways.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <span class="text-3xl" aria-hidden="true">🧬</span>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">Naturally Occurring</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed">
          Peptides are found throughout the body. Insulin is one of the most well-known peptide-based medicines.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <span class="text-3xl" aria-hidden="true">🔭</span>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">An Evolving Field</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed">
          Peptide therapeutics represent a growing area of clinical research and medical interest globally.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <span class="text-3xl" aria-hidden="true">🏥</span>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">Regulated Access</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed">
          In Australia, certain peptide therapies are accessed via the TGA&rsquo;s SAS-B or Authorised Prescriber
          pathways &mdash; through a registered doctor.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
